column3:
Our Milwaukee Packout Mount is the perfect storage solution for your Kawasaki Ridge. This is our rear mount, designed to sit near the back of your bed, close to the tailgate. It installs using existing mounting holes along with four self-drilling screws. Installation is quick and easy—just remove the bed bolts and replace them with the supplied bolts, then use the four provided self-drilling screws to secure the rear of the mount to the bed. We CNC laser cut each mount in-house from 10-gauge P.O. steel and finish it with a black powder coat.

  • Perfect Storage Solution
  • Rear mount towards your tailgate
  • Fit Kawasaki Ridge
  • Easy Install
  • Many Milwaukee options
  • Fits two large Packout Boxes
  • Made in USA

SKU: 200657

This mount works with Kawasaki Ridge, along with any other model that has the same bed configuration.  It is designed to bolt in the rear of your bed closes to the tailgate.  It uses 2 factory bolt holes and then also 4 self-drilling bolts that you drill in your bed. 

Keep your Milwaukee Packout boxes secure with our Packout lock.

Milwaukee offers a wide variety of tool boxes—each one stackable and available in multiple sizes. They even offer a large cooler.

column2: CF Moto UForce U10 Front Bumper
column3:
Give your CF Moto UForce U10 the protection it deserves with our heavy-duty front bumper, built to withstand tough terrain and demanding workloads. This bumper is engineered for durability, bolting directly to the front of the machine.  Light up the night sky with the ability to move the front auxiliary lights to our bumper and our optional cube lights.  

  • Cube Light Option
  • Color Match Accent Option
  • Fits factory bumper lights
  • Mild Textured powder coat
  • Made in USA

SKU: 200647

Designed for both function and strength, our CF Moto UForce Front Bumper features the ability to move the factory bumper lights to our heavy duty bumper and the option of adding our cube lights as an option.  You are able to select your color above for our accent pieces.  These colors are factory colors and are pop riveted on the bumper.   

Our Front Bumper is a three piece design with the bumper extensions bolting on the sides of the bumper with the supplied hardware. We CNC laser cut and bent this bumper from 10 gauge steel and then weld this bumper for a perfect fit on your machine.   After the bumper is welded we then give it a rugged mild texture black powder coat for a lasting finish.  All hardware is supplied to install this bumper on your machine including the hardware to move your auxiliary lights to the bumper.  

Customization Options:

  • Integrated Lighting: Upgrade with flush-mount 3” cube lights, complete with a wiring harness for easy installation. If lighting isn’t needed, a hexagon cover provides a seamless look with an option to upgrade later.
  • Accent Plates: Adds a touch of color while enhancing the style.

Available in color-matched CF Moto UForce U10 finishes for a factory-perfect look.  You are able to reuse the factory winch fairlead.

column2: CF Moto UForce U10 Inner Fender Guards
column3:
Our CF Moto UForce U10 Inner Fender Guards are built to keep branches, rocks, and other debris from coming through your wheel wells. Designed to protect your front inner fenders, each guard is CNC bent from 1/8" thick aluminum for a precise fit on your machine. After they are bent we then stitch weld some areas for maximum strength.  They fit tight to the plastic inner fenders, and are engineered for maximum strength. These guards will not affect tire size and pair perfectly with our Rock Sliders. Their oversized design covers the largest possible area of your inner fenders for superior protection.

  • Heavy Duty
  • Direct Bolt-On
  • Does Not Affect Tire Size
  • Powder-coated Black
  • Made from 1/8″ Aluminum
  • Sold as a Set
  • Made in the USA

SKU 200649

Installation is quick and easy.  We send install directions with every set.  You will need to drill 1/4" holes through your plastic fender well to bolt our inner fenders on. 

Sold as a set for driver and passenger sides.
column37: CF Moto UForce U10 Inner Fender Guards | AJK Offroad
column38: Our CF Moto UForce U10 Inner Fender Guards are built to keep debris from coming through your wheel wells. Designed to protect your front inner fenders.

The tray itself is CNC laser cut and formed from .125" thick aluminum and bolts securely to the side brackets. For added strength, three welded braces reinforce the underside of the tray. Maximize the storage of your Kawasaki with our Kawasaki Ridge bed drawer, designed for both the 2 and 4 seater models. This innovative storage solution allows for easy access to items at the back of your bed, ensuring convenience and efficiency on every adventure.

Engineered for strength and durability, our bed drawer is securely bolted to your machine using existing mounting points.  It features heavy-duty drawer slides rated for 500 lbs per set, with a locking mechanism in both the open and closed positions for stability.

Crafted from CNC laser-cut .125-inch aluminum, the drawer is reinforced with three welded braces for added strength and powder-coated black. Additionally, the drawer offers multiple tie-down points, making it easy to secure your gear with standard ratchet straps or bungee cords.

For added versatility, our drawer is designed to accommodate up to four full-size Milwaukee Packout mounts. If you’d like to include the optional Packout mounts that fit this drawer, simply select the option above. All necessary hardware is included for a seamless installation.

Upgrade your Kawasaki Ridge with the AJK Offroad Bed Drawer—built for strength, functionality, and the toughest terrains.

column3:
Our RUGGED Polaris Xpedition Spare Tire Carrier is a great way to bring your spare tire on the trail while still able to utilize the bed.  If you don't want to bring your spare tire this rack is also great to carrier your gear for that weekend getaway.  Our Spare Tire Carrier / Bed Rack offers many different tie down locations to be able to strap down your tire or cargo for that weekend getaway. 

  • Made in the USA

SKU: 200622

The top rack is roughly 30" deep by 51" wide and easily able to hold a 32" tire.  This Rack is designed to work with most 12V electric coolers and has roughly 19.5" of clearance between the bed and bottom lip of the rack.  This cargo rack is a 3 piece design that is designed to take the abuse that you give your machine.  Our upright legs are bent into a "C" for the most strength and then fully welded.  The sides of the top rack are also bent into a "C" for optimal strength and welded fully.  We also add internal bracing to the top rack so you can carry anything you would like on this rack and not need to worry about the rack failing.  

We have spent many hours designing this rack and added the necessary support and bracing for a very rugged and strong rack.  This is CNC laser cut from .125" thick aluminum and then CNC bent for a perfect fit.  We then weld all seems and give it our mild texture powder coat for a lasting finish. 

You are able to order this rack with or without the lights in the rear of the rack.  If you do not want the lights the rack comes standard with our hexagon inserts to fill the voids of the light holes.  If you order the lights we supply all the wiring to hook your lights into the pulse bar in the front of the machine.  You are also able to select if you want our spare tire strap that is able to hook onto this rack to hold your spare tire.  Please select the options below.

We have designed our Polaris Xpedition Rear Mud Guards to help keep the mud out of your engine bay.  If you have ever been in mud with your Xpedition you know that your engine bay will fill up with mud.  We have designed our mud guards to hep keep the mud out of the engine bay.  These are sold as a set for your driver and passenger side.  They are installed if front of your rear tires and do not effect your tire size.  

This is a fairly simple install and all hardware is included.  You will need to use our self drilling screws and drill them in the round tubing of your frame to hold our mud guards in place.  You will also need to drill a 1/4" hole in your inner plastic fender to help hold the mud guard in place.

column2: Tubing Adapter / Threaded Bung - Off Road Truck, Jeep, ATV, SXS Part
column3:
• Great for link bars and steering bars
  • Easy to adjust and tighten your jam nut with the hex
  • American made 1018 steel
  • Inside threads are threaded completely through
  • Tube Diameter Outside: 1.50" hex Inside 1.00" hex

CNC-machined in the USA

The AJK Off Road tubing adapters are precision CNC-machined for optimal performance on your off road rig. The inside threads are threaded completely through every threaded bung for max holding strength. You don’t need to worry about threads not holding, each tubing adapter is machined from 1018 hex steel. Each threaded bung has a sizable weld chamfer and also a lead chamfer for ease of welding in your tubing. Each left hand threaded tubing bung has a small identification ring so you know what one is left hand and which one is right hand.  These are great for four-link bars and hydraulic assist steering.

*TIP* When welding, you can overheat the tubing adapter and your rod end will not fit in correctly. Make sure welder is set to the correct settings. Too much heat can warp threads. Check your threads before you weld the tubing adapter into the tube.

We also offer other tubing products, including, Go Pro Tubing Mounts, Tubing Disconnects, and Tubing End Caps.

Includes: SKU# - 200136, SKU# - 200137, SKU# - 200119, SKU# - 200120, SKU# - 200116, SKU# - 200117, SKU# - 200133, and SKU# - 200134.

column2: Polaris RZR Prop Shaft Builder Kit
column3:
Now you can build your own custom-length prop shaft with our Polaris RZR Prop Shaft Builder Kit. This kit includes all seven essential driveshaft components to make your custom-length shaft, giving you everything you need to create the perfect fit for your ride. Please note: only the parts shown in the image are included.

  • Fits Polaris RZR XP Turbo 2016
  • Fits Polaris RZR Turbo S 2018+
  • Complete set of yokes
  • Weld to fit your machine
  • Designed for 1.26 ID tubing
  • Made in the USA

SKU: #200468

Details

All of our parts are precision-machined in-house before being sent out to be broached to tighter specifications than factory standards. Once broached, the yokes undergo heat treatment to RC 45, making them stronger than factory parts while maintaining durability without brittleness. These components have been rigorously tested on top-tier rock bouncers and race machines, delivering outstanding performance.

To ensure a perfect U-joint fit, all U-joint holes are precisely machined after heat treatment to maintain tight tolerances. This kit is specifically designed for a 1210 series U-joint, providing the reliability and strength you need.

Compatibility

This kit fits the Polaris RZR XP Turbo (2016 or later) and the Polaris RZR Turbo S (2018 or later).

Additionally, this kit is designed for 1.26 inside diameter tubing.

Please note: U-joints are not included. We recommend Spicer U-joints 5-443X. U-joint straps are also not included. Lastly, this kit does not include tubing.

This kit is only sold with the 7 pieces in the pictures.

CNC machined in the USA

No more zip ties! Our American Made brake line clamps are a must for anyone that has ever twisted a brake line off their rig. These tough little brackets will hold your line's out of harm's way.

Each brake line clamp is CNC-machined from 6061-T6 aluminum. The clamps will give any rig a finishing touch while setting you apart from other off road trucks, jeeps, ATV's, or 4X4's.

Based on the size option you select above, the clamp will fit around 1.0", 1.25", 1.50", 1.75” or 2.00” bars to hold your line's or any other wires out of harm's way. This clamp has a 5/16 hole for your line to clamp to. Each clamp comes with one, ¼-20 socket head cap screw to clamp the two pieces together.

Finally, AJK Offroad uses coarse thread bolts in aluminum, making them less likely to strip out. Each clamp is ½” thick.

column3:
• Made from 2.25″ DOM tubing
  • .125” wall
  • 2.00” inside diameter
  • Includes two ⅜” bolts and two nylon locking nuts

 

CNC-machined in the USA for increased accuracy, not laser cut.

Each Weld on Bump Stop can is precision CNC-machined, not laser cut, for increased accuracy. Made from 2.25" tubing with a .125" wall for a 2.00" inside diameter. After it's machined, we weld on the brackets for the socket head cap screws.

Each piece comes supplied with two ⅜" bolts and two nylon locking nuts.

We use a simple, but very effective clamping design our engineers have run through countless tests on their own off road rigs. Fits most 2.0" bump stop cans.

*TIP* When welding you can overheat the bump stop can which can cause it to not fit correctly. Make sure welder is set to the correct settings. Too much heat can warp the part. Check to make sure your bump stop fits properly in the bump stop can before you weld the can on your frame.

Check out our base clamps and tubing end caps to pair with your bump stop can.

column3:
• Uses MALE DIAMOND KNURLS
  • Made from 6061-T6 Billet Aluminum
  • Uses ½” hardened Zinc plated stud with wing nut
  • Clamps around tubing using two ¼-20 SHCS
  • SOLD INDIVIDUALLY

Every Hi-Lift Mount/Clamp uses MALE DIAMOND KNURLS for a secure hold on the tube you are clamping.

A male diamond knurl helps hold the clamp in both directions from moving.  We use two ¼-20 SHCS to hold the two pieces together.  This clamp can be mounted on any size tubing listed above.  This is a clean way to mount your Hi-Lift on your roll cage, bumper or any other tubing.

You simply take each half of the clamp and bolt each side around the tubing where you want your Hi-Lift to be mounted and tighten the supplied bolts. Then set your Hi-Lift Jack on the two studs protruding from the clamps and use the supplied wing nut to secure your Hi-Lift to the clamp.

We machine these Hi-Lift Clamps/brackets in house from 6061-T6 billet aluminum.  Every AJK Offroad part is proud to be designed and manufactured in the USA.

Our off road tubing disconnects work great to protect your engine and other vital component on your rig. These flat tubing disconnects work great on bumpers, roll cages, and removable racks.  Our offroad tubing disconnects work great on about any off-road vehicle including your Jeep, tube buggy and side by side.

AJK Offroad tubing disconnects can be mounted close to other components by having both bolts start from the same direction.  We use two 3/8-16 SHCS to hold the two pieces together.

CNC-machined in the USA

AJK Offroad has designed the tubing disconnect to interlock with three different locking points. We use two ⅜-16" diameter, socket head cap screws to hold the two pieces together for additional stability.

Both bolts start from the same direction, so you can mount the tubing disconnect closer to the vital components you need to protect.

Our tubing disconnects protect your engine and other vital components. They also are widely used for bumpers, roll cages, and removable racks. Product will work on virtually any off-road vehicle including your Jeep, tube buggy and side by side.

AJK Offroad works with trusted partners to develop these interlocking tubing disconnects. Every tubing disconnect is created from 1018 steel purchased from companies based in the USA. We drill and tap the pieces to the standard specs of the bolt for optimum holding strength.

The end that inserts in the tubing has a large weld chamfer for a nice weld and is long enough to properly align with the tubing.

Every tubing coupler is made from 1018 American-made steel. Based on your sizing option selected above, the tubing disconnect will fit inside a 1.50” or 1.75" OD tubing with wall thickness of .120”.

column3:

  • SOLD IN PACKAGE OF 2 PCS

 

CNC-machined in the USA for increased accuracy, not laser cut.

Each Weld on Bump Stop can is precision CNC-machined, not laser cut, for increased accuracy. Made from 2.25" tubing with a .125" wall for a 2.00" inside diameter.  After it's machined, we weld on the brackets for the socket head cap screws.

Each piece comes supplied with two ⅜" bolts and two nylon locking nuts.

We use a simple, but very effective clamping design our engineers have run through countless tests on their own off road rigs. Fits must 2.0" bump stop cans.

*TIP* When welding you can overheat the bump stop can which can cause it to not fit correctly. Make sure welder is set to the correct settings. Too much heat can warp the part. Check to make sure your bump stop fits properly in the bump stop can before you weld the can on your frame.

Check out our base clamps and tubing end caps to pair with your bump stop can.

column2: Offroad Rugged X-Grip Phone / Tablet Mount for Roll Cage
column3:
• American made
  • Comes with Ram Mounts X-Grip
  • Each clamp is 1/2″ thick
  • Great way to mount your phone to any tubing
  • Made from 6061-T6 Billet Aluminum

Our Offroad Rugged X-Grip phone holder and tablet mounts are American Made for the extreme off road use.  Our phone mount or tablet mount can be fitted to any Jeep, truck, ATV, UTV, or side-by-side.

We have taken the popular Ram Mount X-Grip phone holder and tablet mount and made it even better.  Our aluminum mount was designed to work specifically with Ram Mounts 1" rubber ball.  Our billet aluminum mount will fit .875", 1.00", 1.25", 1.50", 1.75", and 2.00" diameter tubing and also .75" and 1.00" square tubing.  We then mate our billet aluminum mount to Ram Mounts 1" ball.

Ram Mounts is a leader of rugged and versatile mounting solutions for electronics.  Ram Mounts uses an elastomeric rubber ball that incorporates a non-slip function and shock and vibration dampening.  We have partnered with Ram Mounts because of there high standard of quality and performance.

Based on the size options you select above, the clamp will fit around .875", 1.00", 1.25", 1.50", 1.75", or 2.00" bars along with .75" and 1.00" square bars to hold your phone or tablet on any roll cage, dash bar, or any other tubing.  Each Ram mount is able to articulate to many different positions to make sure that your phone or tablet is right where you need it.

This mount is supplied with one aluminum tubing mount and one Ram Mount phone holder with rubber spider web holder or one tablet mount.

We offer four different sizes of Ram Mounts:

Our small Ram mount phone holder will accept a phone width from 1.875" to 3.25"

Our large Ram mount phone holder will accept a phone width from 1.75" to 4.50"

Our small Ram mount tablet holder will accept a tablet width from 2.50" to 5.75"

Our large Ram mount tablet holder will accept a tablet width from 6.25" to 8.10" and 10.25" long

column3:
• Uses nylon washers and bushings to eliminate noise
  • Heavy duty pull pin
  • Quick spring release
  • Made from 6061-T6 billet aluminum
  • Able to be used with our base clamps
  • Hose clamps included

Please Select Options Below for Pricing


We here at AJK Offroad have put a lot of time and research into our offroad fire extinguisher mount.  We have taken extreme measures to make sure that every component fits and functions properly for high quality, quick release mount.

Specifically designed from billet aluminum and machined in the USA with tight tolerances. Our design uses nylon bushing, washers, and springs. This design eliminates the noise from vibration and keeps dirt and grime away from the moving parts.  We use a ½” diameter heavy duty, spring loaded pull pin for a quick, smooth, and effortless release.  Please choose from our base clamp options.  Our universal strap clamp will fit around your stock Jeep roll cage for a tight and secure fit, or use our standard base clamps for 1.50", 1.75," or 2.00" diameter tubing.

This Fire Extinguisher mount can be used with our base clamps part # 200130, 200131, and 200141 or also our universal strap clamp part #200156.  Our clamps bolt directly to the bottom side of this Fire Extinguisher Mount and are able to mount to different sizes of tubing for a clean uniform look.  You can also mount this using the four 1/4” holes to your floor board, dash, inside fender or any other flat surface.

We are offering this Fire Extinguisher Mount in raw aluminum, red, and black anodize.  Select your color above.

Every mount comes with our high quality, heavy duty, stainless steel hose clamps.

This Quick Shot Fire Extinguisher Mount is a must for your performance offroad vehicle.

Our short off road tubing disconnects work great for your SXS bumpers, roll cages, and removable racks. These flat tubing disconnects also work great to protect your engine and other vital components of your rig.  Our offroad tubing disconnects work great on about any off-road vehicle including your UTV, Jeep, tube buggy, and side by side.

AJK Offroad tubing disconnects can be mounted close to other components by having both bolts start from the same direction.  We use two 3/8-16 SHCS to hold the two pieces together.  These are short in length for you to be able to weld them closer to the bends of your tube.

The tubing disconnect contains a radius for you to be able to weld your tubing at any angle.  These work great for tight angles where our standard disconnects will not fit.  We CNC machine these in house from 1018 steel.

We have designed this Honda Talon Spare Tire Carrier to handle a 35" tire. This will bolt directly to the stock roll cage.  The spare tire carrier clamps to the back roll cage pillar and uses a gas shock to help lift the tire.  It is hinged in two different spots and uses two spring loaded locking pins.  Each hinge has a locking spring pin.  The locking spring pin allows the spare tire carrier to stay in three different positions.  With this spare tire hinging it allows you to have access to your bed and still carrier a spare tire.   This spare tire carrier uses a "Y" strap to hold your spare tire on the carrier.

 

IT IS NOT RECOMMENDED TO TRAVEL WITH THE TIRE IN THE UP POSITION.

The AJK Off Road tubing adapters are precision CNC-machined for optimal performance on your off road rig. The inside threads are threaded completely through every threaded bung for max holding strength. You don’t need to worry about threads not holding, each tubing adapter is machined from 1018 steel. Each threaded bung has a sizable weld chamfer and also a lead chamfer for ease of welding in your tubing.  This tubing adapter has 3/8-24 threads thru.

*TIP* When welding, you can overheat the tubing adapter and your bolt will not fit in correctly. Make sure welder is set to the correct settings. Too much heat can warp threads. Check your threads before you weld the tubing adapter into the tube.

READ DESCRIPTION BELOW

We offer many different options for our front Can-Am X3 grill.  These Can-Am X3 grills are CNC Laser cut from plate aluminum and then powder coated.  This is a simple and easy install.  Simply remove your stock grill and bolt our grill together, then use the six longer bolts to bolt in the factory location.  No drilling required.  All hardware is stainless steel and supplied.  Please look at the six different pictures to determine the X3 grill that you would like.  The back grill color is offset from the front grill to make the color stand out. Our back and front ring colors are Blue, Orange, White, and Red.

Here is a run down of the different options:

B-12 Grill Base:  Black Powder coat, Hexagon shape.  (1 piece)

B-12 Grill Base with back color:  B-12 grill with additional back plate that shows thru on the bottom of the hexagon.  (2 pieces)

B-12 Grill Base with back color and front ring: B-12 grill with back plate and front ring,  Back plate and front ring are color matched.  (3 pieces)

B-18 Grill Base:  Black Power coat, Square shape.  (1 piece)

B-18 Grill Base with back color:  B-18 grill with the back color show thru on two sides of the square shape.  (2 pieces)

B-18 Grill Base with back color and front ring:  B-18 grill with back plate and front ring.  Back plate and front ring are color matched.  (3 pieces)

 

Call with any questions during normal business hours.

The picture that is shown is the correct picture of the options you chose.

We have designed our Baja style front Can-Am X3 bumper to look good and take the abuse a front bumper needs to take.  Our front X3 bumper is made from 1.50" Dia .095 wall DOM tubing along with 1.25" Dia .095 wall DOM tubing and is fully tig welded.  The tube ends are capped with our billet aluminum push in end caps.  This bumper bolts to the bottom A arms and also the front bar in front of your radiator.  Our Baja Style front bumper is a very strong bumper and is very easy to install.  All Hardware is included with the bumper.

We offer two different types of powder coat for this X3 bumper.  The Texture black powder coat is a perfect match to your stock roll cage with the fine texture.  We also offer a smooth black powder coat.

We offer two different style of lights for this bumper.  We offer a Heiss 8" light bar that bolts in the center of the bumper, or we offer Heiss cube lights that bolt on the outsides of the bumper.  You are able to bolt both style of lights to the front bumper at the same time.  All hardware and wiring is supplied with the lights.

We manufacture each Hitch Skid from 2"x2" square tube with a 1/4" wall thickness. A 10"x10" 1/4" steel plate is fully MIG welded to the square tube, and our recovery clevis is welded directly to the plate and tube for maximum strength. The 2"x2" square tube features four different mounting pin holes, providing versatility across a variety of applications.

Every Hitch Skid comes standard with a recovery point. The clevis mount is .875" thick with a 1" bore, making it the perfect fit for a standard 3/4" shackle. column2: Polaris Pro R / Turbo R High Clearance Radius Rods
column3:
Upgrade your ride with Polaris Pro R / Turbo R High Clearance Radius Rods, engineered for maximum durability and ground clearance. Designed for extreme terrain, these rods are precision-machined from 6061-T6 billet aluminum for strength, stability, and performance.

  • Heavy Duty
  • Made from 6061-T6 Aluminum
  • 3.2″ Additional Ground Clearance
  • 1.375″ Thick 1.75″ Tall
  • Upper Rod is 1.25 HEX
  • Fully Adjustable Upper Rod
  • Lifetime Warranty
  • Made in the USA

The lower radius rods feature a 1.375” thick, 1.75” tall profile, delivering an additional 3.2” of ground clearance to navigate over rocks, ruts, and obstacles with ease. The upper radius rods are made from 1.25” 6061-T6 hex material and are fully adjustable on both ends for a perfect fit.

Key Features:

  • Billet Aluminum Construction: Machined for durability and precision.
  • Pre-Set Upper Rods: Adjustability with factory-length preset for easy installation.
  • 304 Stainless Steel Misalignment Spacers: Wear-resistant for long-lasting performance.
  • Billet Aluminum Radius Rod Plate: SOLD SEPERATLY Adds extra strength and a clean, custom look.

Choose from upper-only, lower-only, or a full set of four. Available in factory-matched Polaris Pro R / Turbo R colors or raw aluminum.

A lifetime warranty included for the original owner (excluding rod ends and misalignment spacers, which are wear items).

column3:
The plastic front bumper on your Polaris Pro R is prone to damage from regular trail use. As you may know, over time, exposure to the elements causes plastic to become increasingly brittle. With continued wear, your bumper becomes more susceptible to breaking when hit by debris on the trail. This is where our Polaris Pro R Front Bumper comes into play as an essential replacement part.

  • Protects your machine
  • Looks great
  • Winch frame made from 1/4″ plate
  • Bumper plate cut from 11 gauge
  • CNC Laser Cut
  • CNC Bent
  • Made in the USA
  • Does not fit 25 and new machines

SKU: 200483

The Build

For this bumper design, we prioritized functionality, durability, and style. We incorporated the ability to mount a winch, ensured robust front-end protection, and created a design that enhances the overall appearance of your machine.

The bumper features a 1/4" thick framework combined with an 11-gauge steel outer shell. This construction provides excellent protection against debris like sticks and rocks, as well as minor collisions. The winch is mounted using a separate bracket that bolts directly to your machine behind the bumper. This design ensures the bumper safeguards both the winch and your vehicle. Additionally, the bracket is compatible with various winch models, offering flexibility to meet your needs.

To complete the design, we applied a durable black powder coat finish. This not only adds a sleek, professional look but also protects the bumper from rust and corrosion, ensuring it performs and looks great for years to come.

This bumper roughly weighs 30 lbs without the winch attached.

Options

Our bumper is compatible with any of our Warn Winches. These winches come in Warn Axon 5500 LBS, Warn VRX 4500 LBS, or Warn VRX 3500 LBS. Warn winches are top of their class and have proven to be reliable under all conditions, even when submerged in water (IP68 rating). Warn winches come with everything you need to use them. For specifics of each winch, click the bolded links above. With a winch, we highly suggest one of our billet aluminum fairleads or a raw aluminum fairlead. Both accent nicely with the black bumper.

The bumper always comes with a winch mounting bracket, even if you don't purchase the winch. Other winch models will also work with our bumper.

Installation

Our design uses the pre-existing mount holes found on your Pro R. Unbolt the stock bumper and bolt ours on. Our Polaris Pro R bumper will require you to cut some of the plastic hidden behind the bumper. This cut can be easily done with a utility blade. If you decide you would like to go back to the original factory bumper you will still be able to use the factory bumper.

The gas cap on the stock KRX is not in a good spot to say the least. It is recessed in the machine, very low to the ground, and next to the front tires. No other manufacturer has done this for their gas caps because it gets them covered in mud. Our KRX fuel door is a well priced and easy to install solution to this problem.  Our Kawasaki KRX gas cap cover offers the hinge on the top of the plate to make sure the cover will stay closed during any style of riding.

Our Kawasaki KRX fuel door is CNC laser cut and bent from lightweight aluminum. For the best looking and long lasting finish we powder coat our door black. To finish it off we install our spring loaded hinge. This spring provides more than enough force to hold the fuel door against your machine so there is no rattling from our part. Overall, our Kawasaki KRX Fuel Door keeps your gas cap accessible and clean.

This mount comes with all necessary hardware.

column3:
Our Polaris Xpedition Bed Tray is an excellent way to increase your machine’s cargo capacity. Compatible with both the Polaris Xpedition XP and ADV models, this tray effectively doubles your available storage space. It’s designed to bolt directly onto the side of your bed using the factory aluminum bed rails. The side brackets can be installed in either a low or high position—offering a little over 11" of clearance underneath in the low setting, or approximately 15.5" in the high setting.  Select option below if you want the bed mat along with packout mounts.

 

  • Doubles your bed storage space
  • Works with both the XP and ADV
  • Two different height options
  • Mounts on the side of your bed
  • Easy install
  • Powder-coated black
  • Able to order with Tray Mat
  • All hardware included
  • Made in USA


SKU 200537

The side brackets mount to the bed using our custom nuts, which insert into the factory aluminum bed rails. Each bracket is CNC laser cut from 10-gauge steel, CNC bent, and powder-coated black for durability. The tray itself is CNC laser cut and formed from .125" thick aluminum and bolts securely to the side brackets. For added strength, three welded braces reinforce the underside of the tray. It also features multiple tie-down points, compatible with standard small ratchet straps or bungee cords. Every component is powder-coated black for long-lasting use, and all hardware is included.

We have now added a Terick Solutions Tray Mat that fits perfect in our drawer.  This mat is very heavy duty and is almost 3/8" thick.  This mat fits in the Tray and does not come with the holes for the packout mounts.  If you order the packout mounts you will need to cut the holes in the mat for the packouts.   The Mat will offer the same milling pattern as the floor mats from Terick Solutions and they look great together.

Some pictures are shown with our Polaris Xpedition Bed Drawer,  which is not included with the tray.

Our short off road tubing disconnects work great for your SXS bumpers, roll cages, and removable racks. These flat tubing disconnects also work great to protect your engine and other vital components of your rig.  Our offroad tubing disconnects work great on about any off-road vehicle including your UTV, Jeep, tube buggy, and side by side.

Our Polaris Xpedition Rock Sliders are built to take a beating and keep your ride protected. These low-profile sliders are designed to guard your plastics and help your machine glide smoothly over rocks that would otherwise cause damage. Crafted from durable 10-gauge plate steel, each slider is CNC laser-cut and precision-bent to match the contour of your vehicle. We finish them with a tough black powder coat for long-lasting performance and a sleek look. Each set includes threaded studs that mount directly to your factory frame for a secure fit. You’ll need to cut holes in your plastic panels to allow the studs to pass through cleanly. Once installed, just bolt the sliders onto the studs and reattach the lower skid plate bolts. All necessary hardware is included.

column2: Tubing Disconnect - Interlocking Tubing Coupler - Off Road Trucks, Jeeps, ATV, SXS
column3:
• Flexibility to easily remove the tubing to access motor, transmission
  • Two 3/8-16 SHCS are included for assembly
  • Made from 1018 mild steel
  • Three tier interlocking system
  • Both bolts start from the same side for ease of installation
  • Sizeable weld chamfers

CNC-machined in the USA

AJK Offroad has designed the tubing disconnect to interlock with three different locking points. We use two ⅜-16" diameter, socket head cap screws to hold the two pieces together for additional stability.

Both bolts start from the same direction, so you can mount the tubing disconnect closer to the vital components you need to protect.

Our tubing disconnects protect your engine and other vital components. They also are widely used for bumpers, roll cages, and removable racks. Product will work on virtually any off-road vehicle including your Jeep, tube buggy and side by side.

AJK Offroad works with trusted partners to develop these interlocking tubing disconnects. Every tubing disconnect is created from 1018 steel purchased from companies based in the USA. We drill and tap the pieces to the standard specs of the bolt for optimum holding strength.

The end that inserts in the tubing has a large weld chamfer for a nice weld and is long enough to properly align with the tubing.

Every tubing coupler is made from 1018 American-made steel. Based on your sizing option selected above, the tubing disconnect will fit inside a 1.50” or 1.75" OD tubing with wall thickness of .120”.

SKU# - 200112
SKU# - 200113

Our Chainsaw Mount will work with any SXS, UTV or any vehicle with a standard size roll bar.  Each chainsaw mount is made from heavy duty HDPE Plastic and Billet Aluminum.  This HDPE is high impact resistant plastic and works great to protect the teeth on your chainsaw.  Each mount comes with our Billet Aluminum base clamps that will fit 1.50", 1.75", 1.875", and 2.00" tubing.  We also offer this mount with our Billet Aluminum Universal mount that will fit any size roll bar.

You simply bolt the mount to your rollbar and insert your chainsaw in the open slot and tighten the two supplied thumb screws to hold your chainsaw in place.

This will accept a chainsaw with a bar 3.50" tall by .50" wide.  Most chainsaws will fit in this mount.

column3:
Our Battery Terminal Relocation Kit is designed to move your battery terminals to a more accessible location for easier maintenance. Some factory battery placements can be difficult to reach, and this kit provides a clean, practical solution. Each bracket is CNC laser-cut from 11-gauge steel and finished with a durable black powder coat. The terminals are secured with a large serrated nut and feature a notched cover that locks into place for added protection.

  • Perfect for Can-am
  • 4 gauge cable
  • Great for trickle charge
  • Heavy duty
  • Laser cut and CNC bent
  • Powder coated
  • Made in USA

We offer this kit with or without battery cables. Each cable is made from 4-gauge wire and measures 18" long, allowing you to relocate your terminals up to 18" away from the battery.

This kit works especially well for the Can-Am X3, where the battery is located under the seat and can be difficult to access. It can be mounted directly behind the battery on the outside of the machine for convenient reach.

Standard roll cage clamps don't give you the flexibility to mount on the "A" pillar of your machine. The angle on the "A" pillar makes most mounts useless. With our adjustable clamp you can compensate for the "A" pillar angle when mounting.

Our Adjustable roll cage clamp is designed to rotate every 22.5 degrees using a dual pin system. This system ensures zero adjustment during riding after you set your clamp.

Our clamp is made with 6061-T6 billet aluminum for the best weight to strength ratio. Overall, our clamp will never budge, after being set, even under the harshest conditions.

Our adjustable light bar clamp is sold individually.

column3:
Take your Polaris Xpedition to the next level with the AJK Offroad Bed Drawer—the ultimate solution for secure, organized, and accessible storage. Designed to fit seamlessly in your Xpedition's bed, this rugged, heavy-duty drawer keeps your gear protected from the elements while ensuring everything you need is right at your fingertips. Whether you're an overlander, hunter, or weekend warrior, this durable storage system helps you stay prepared for any adventure.  Select option below if you want the bed mat along with packout mounts.

  • Heavy-Duty Draw Slides
  • Works with Both the XP and ADV
  • Extends 26" Out
  • Locking Draw Slides
  • Powder Coated Black
  • All Hardware Included
  • Able to order with Drawer Mat
  • Made in the USA

SKU: 200529

Maximize the storage of your Polaris with our Polaris Xpedition bed drawer, designed for both the Polaris Xpedition XP and ADV models. This innovative storage solution allows for easy access to items at the back of your bed, ensuring convenience and efficiency on every adventure.

Engineered for strength and durability, our bed drawer is securely bolted to your machine using existing mounting points. On the ADV model you will need to drill through your bed mat or remove your bed mat to bolt the drawer slides in place. It features heavy-duty drawer slides rated for 500 lbs per set, with a locking mechanism in both the open and closed positions for stability.

Crafted from CNC laser-cut .125-inch aluminum, the drawer is reinforced with three welded braces for added strength and powder-coated black. The CNC laser-cut 10-gauge steel brackets holding the slides are powder-coated black for superior durability and corrosion resistance. Additionally, the drawer offers multiple tie-down points, making it easy to secure your gear with standard ratchet straps or bungee cords.

We have now added a Terick Solutions Drawer Mat that fits perfect in our drawer.  This mat is very heavy duty and is almost 3/8" thick.  This mat fits in the drawer and does not come with the holes for the packout mounts.  If you order the packout mounts you will need to cut the holes in the mat for the packouts.   The Mat will offer the same milling pattern as the floor mats from Terick Solutions and they look great together.

For added versatility, our drawer is designed to accommodate two full-size Milwaukee Packout mounts. If you’d like to include the optional Packout trays that fit this drawer, simply select the option above. All necessary hardware is included for a seamless installation.

Upgrade your Polaris Xpedition with the AJK Offroad Bed Drawer—built for strength, functionality, and the toughest terrains.

Some pictures are shown with our Polaris Xpedition Bed Tray. Please note that the bed tray is not included with the drawer, and is sold separately.

Our Polaris Xpedition Exhaust Cover makes the rear end of your Xpedition look great.  Our main frame work of the exhaust cover is CNC Laser cut and bent from 16 gauge steel and powder coated black.  We then add our hexagon vents to the framework.  We offer the vents in Factory Polaris colors.  We also also the hexagon vent in raw steel for you to paint the color of your choice.

This Exhaust Cover replaces the cheap plastic cover and uses the factory holes so no drilling is required.  We supply all the hardware to install this great looking cover.  Along with the supplied hardware we also supply nice aluminum body washers to give your Exhaust Cover the finished look.

** If you have the factory Polaris Tube Bumper you will need to shim the top of the bumper out to fit our Exhaust cover.

Our Exhaust Cover and our Rear Bumper look great together.
